{
  "abstract": "The abstract is on Page 1 of the document. It states the purpose of the study was to formulate double-layer tablets of lornoxicam (LRX) by direct compression and evaluate their physical and drug release characteristics. The outer layer contained an immediate-release dose (4 mg) with MCC, starch, and lactose. The cores for sustained release used HPMC, PVP K90, and carbomer. The analytical method (UV spectroscopy) was validated for linearity, precision, accuracy, recovery, and specificity. Results showed HPMC-based cores had better flow properties. Drug release followed the Higuchi kinetic model via diffusion/polymer relaxation or diffusion/erosion. The conclusion was that these tablets are suitable for treating inflammatory conditions.",
  "introduction": "The introduction is on Pages 1 and 2. It discusses the advantages of controlled drug delivery systems and the need for an initial fast release followed by a sustained release for drugs like NSAIDs. It introduces double-layer tablets as a solution for biphasic release. It describes lornoxicam (LRX) as an NSAID from the oxicam family with a half-life of 3-4 hours, used for postoperative pain. The aim was to design a double-layer tablet with a 4 mg immediate-release outer layer and a 12 mg sustained-release core to improve bioavailability and patient compliance.",
  "materials_and_methods": {
    "materials_origin": {
      "Lornoxicam (LRX)": "Abdi Ibrahim Ilac A.S. (Turkey)",
      "Carbomer (Carbopol 971P NF)": "Lubrizol (U.S.A.)",
      "HPMC (Methocel K15 Premium EP)": "Colorcon (England)",
      "Starch 1500": "Colorcon (England)",
      "PVP K90 (Povidone K90)": "Sigma-Aldrich (Germany)",
      "Lactose anhydrous": "DMV (The Netherlands)",
      "Avicel Type PH-102": "Selectchemie AG (Switzerland)",
      "Magnesium stearate": "Prever (Italy)"
    },
    "experimental_design_for_optimization": "The experimental design involved preparing 8 different core formulations and 8 corresponding double-layer tablet formulations by varying the type and concentration of polymers (HPMC, PVP K90, Carbomer) in the core. The outer layer composition was kept constant. The goal was to optimize the formulation for biphasic release (immediate from outer layer, sustained from core).",
    "ingredients_identification": {
      "preparation": "Tablet cores (100 mg) containing 12 mg LRX were compressed using a hydraulic press under 13790 kPa force with a 7.9 mm flat punch. They were then coated with a 150 mg outer layer containing 4 mg LRX and compressed again using a 10 mm flat punch under 13790 kPa force to form the final 250 mg double-layer tablet.",
      "results": "The method produced tablets with good physical characteristics and biphasic drug release.",
      "equation": "A = 22.894C - 0.078",
      "absorbance": "376 nm"
    },
